SIMPLE: sandwich
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sandwich
<hw>Sand"wich</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named from the
Earl of <ets>Sandwich</ets>.]</ety> <def>Two pieces of bread and butter
with a thin slice of meat, cheese, or the like, between them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- 2. Any food composed of two pieces of bread with another food in
between. 3. Any object composed of two layers of one subtance on either
side of a second substance. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sandwich</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sandwich
<hw>Sand"wich</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Sandwiched</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Sandwiching</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To make into a sandwich;
also, figuratively, to insert between portions of something dissimilar;
to form of alternate parts or things, or alternating layers of a
different nature; to interlard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sandworm</ent>⟦br⟧
